  "body": "# Feature Issue\r\n\r\nCurrently Status.im have a very simple profile system, only allowing to set a name and a ens domain (usually username.stateofus.eth). \r\n\r\n3box.io is using OrbitDB (that uses IPFS) and ethereum to authenticate changes in this DB, that can store users profile in a very flexible way. \r\n\r\n### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I want to have a public profile that I can selectively share with my contacts or with the world. \r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nPossible features:\r\n- Public Profile\r\n- User Public Feeds\r\n- privately contact list backup/sync\r\n- (...) \r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\n\r\n1. Status User profile stored on 3box.io is managed by EIP1581 (non wallet key) \r\n2. Contacts IDs (other EIP1581 pub keys) are allowed to read user profile\r\n\r\n### Notes\r\n\r\nShould only be used for information that is not intended to be absolutely private, but for allowing users that want to share public information with other users. \r\n\r\n### References \r\n\r\n3Box SDK: https://github.com/3box/3box-js/ \r\nIdentityWallet SDK: https://github.com/3box/identity-wallet-js/\r\nAdd new keytypes (EIP1581) to the same system: https://github.com/3box/js-3id-blockchain-utils\r\nDocs: https://docs.3box.io/build/wallets/4.-link-an-address-to-the-identity\r\n\r\nOrbit DB: https://github.com/orbitdb/orbit-db\r\n",
